<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF109-605-169  </DOCNO><DOCID>09 605 169.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>EDN  Oct 18 1990 v35 n21A p34(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Optical drive offers 128 Mbytes on 3 1/2-in. media. (contains arelated article on the future of the 5.25-inch optical format)(Mass Optical Storage Technologies' RMD-5100-S optical disk drive)(product announcement)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Swartz, Eric.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Mass Optical Storage Technologies' (MOST) RMD-5100-S optical diskdrive is the first to offer 128Mbytes on 3.5-inch optical media.andO;Its seek times average 35 msec and data transfer rates reach3Mbytes per second.andP;  Features include a removable erasable media,extensive self diagnostics and a high level of data integrity.andO;The disk fits into a cartridge the size of 3.5-inch floppy disks.andO;They comply with the ANSI/ISO proposed standard for 3.5-inchoptical media and have a 10-year life.andP;  The RMD-5100-S costs$2,425; the media are expected to cost $128.andP;  Volume shipment isscheduled for Jan 1991.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Mass Optical Storage Technologies Inc. (Product introduction).andO;Product:   Mass Optical Storage Technologies RMD-5100-S (Optical disk drive)(Product introduction).andO;Topic:     Optical MemoryProduct IntroductionOptical storage devicesOptical disks.andO;Feature:   illustrationphotograph.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>